                      <h1>Certificate in Condominium Management (16 CEUs)</h1>
           


            <!-- End top content block area -->

          <div id="content-area">
            <div id="node-43810" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <strong>Offered by:</strong> Career &amp; Professional Develop.    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    <strong>Degree:</strong> Certificate in Condominium Management      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Program Requirements</h3>

    
    <p>Condominium development has enjoyed remarkable growth in Quebec over the last decade: the number of Quebec households living in condos is expected to increase to 266,000 by 2016 (in comparison with 155,000 in 2006).  This growth requires qualified professionals who can deal effectively with various aspects of managing a condominium. To address this growing demand, McGill School of Continuing Studies is introducing a new non-credit program, which explores the complex challenges of condominium management and provides participants with information, knowledge, and practical skills.</p>

          <h4>Required Courses</h4>

    
              <p>Note: Students taking this Certificate in English normally take English courses while those taking this Certificate in French normally take French courses.</p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/cbus-100" class="program-course-title">
              CBUS 100 Condominium Financial Management in Quebec (4 CE units)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-19596" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Career &amp; Professional Develop. (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">School of Continuing Studies</a>)</p>
          <p>Administered by: <a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">Centre for Continuing Education</a></p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Business              : Gain the knowledge and skills required to successfully manage all financial aspects of a condominium. The course will explain the responsibilities of the property manager in budgeting, preparation of financial statements, collection, development of a reserve fund, cash-flow planning, preparation for audit and investments. Working knowledge of Excel is required.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Supplementary information: 30 hours of classroom instruction plus approx.10 hours of pre-course readings and assignments</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/cbus-101" class="program-course-title">
              CBUS 101 Gestion financière de la copropriété au Québec (4 CE units)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-19598" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Career &amp; Professional Develop. (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">School of Continuing Studies</a>)</p>
          <p>Administered by: <a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">Centre for Continuing Education</a></p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Business              : Ce cours permet d’acquérir les connaissances nécessaires pour la gestion des aspects financiers d’une copropriété: les responsabilités du gestionnaire en matière de budgétisation, comptabilité, préparation des états financiers, développement du fond de prévoyance, planification du flux de trésorerie, préparation pour la vérification externe et la gestion d’investissements.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Supplementary information: 30 heures en classe plus environ 10 heures de lecture supplémentaire et travaux de cours</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/cbus-102" class="program-course-title">
              CBUS 102 Condominium Law in Quebec (4 CE units)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-19600" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Career &amp; Professional Develop. (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">School of Continuing Studies</a>)</p>
          <p>Administered by: <a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">Centre for Continuing Education</a></p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Business              : This course will explore all aspects of Condominium Law in Quebec and related governance which includes declarations, bylaws, special rules, as well as rules of professional and ethical conduct. The course will cover the legal options and remedies available to Condo Associations in situations of abandoned units and delinquent tenants.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Supplementary information: 30 hours of classroom instruction plus approx.10 hours of pre-course readings and assignments.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/cbus-103" class="program-course-title">
              CBUS 103 Gestion juridique de la copropriété au Québec (4 CE units)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-19602" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Career &amp; Professional Develop. (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">School of Continuing Studies</a>)</p>
          <p>Administered by: <a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">Centre for Continuing Education</a></p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Business              : Ce cours explore les aspects de la loi Québécoise sur les copropriétés et la gouvernance (les déclarations, les règlements,  les règles particulières de conduite professionnelle et éthique).  Les options juridiques et les recours possible du Syndicat de Copropriétés pour les unités laissées vacantes et les locataires en défaut seront explorés.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Supplementary information: 30 heures en classe plus environ 10 heures de lecture supplémentaire et travaux de cours.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/cbus-104" class="program-course-title">
              CBUS 104 Condominium Building and Maintenance Management (4 CE units)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-19604" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Career &amp; Professional Develop. (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">School of Continuing Studies</a>)</p>
          <p>Administered by: <a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">Centre for Continuing Education</a></p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Business              : This course will provide an overview of condominium structures and good maintenance practices. Gain a working knowledge of various building systems including plumbing, heating, ventilation, electricity and security. Learn how to resolve problems and effectively communicate solutions, what to do in emergency situations and how to manage projects involving contractors.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Supplementary information: 30 hours of classroom instruction plus approx.10 hours of pre-course readings and assignments.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/cbus-105" class="program-course-title">
              CBUS 105 Gestion technique du bâtiment de la copropriété (4 CE units)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-19606" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Career &amp; Professional Develop. (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">School of Continuing Studies</a>)</p>
          <p>Administered by: <a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">Centre for Continuing Education</a></p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Business              : Ce cours présente les structures de copropriétés et les bonnes pratiques d’entretien. L’étudiant acquerra des connaissances sur des systèmes comme la plomberie, chauffage et ventilation. La résolution de problèmes, la communication efficace de solutions, la gestion de situations d’urgence et de projets impliquant des métiers de la construction seront présentes.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Supplementary information: 30 heures en classe plus environ 10 heures de lecture supplémentaire et travaux de cours.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/cbus-106" class="program-course-title">
              CBUS 106 Managing Day-to-Day Condominium Operations (4 CE units)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-19608" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Career &amp; Professional Develop. (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">School of Continuing Studies</a>)</p>
          <p>Administered by: <a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">Centre for Continuing Education</a></p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Business              : Gain the knowledge and skills required for efficient day-to-day management of condominium operations, including development of internal policies and procedures, maintenance of condominium records, contract management, organization of meetings and preparation of various documents. Learn how to communicate effectively with internal and external stakeholders and to resolve conflicts.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Supplementary information: 30 hours of classroom instruction plus approx.10 hours of pre-course readings and assignments.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/cbus-107" class="program-course-title">
              CBUS 107 Gestion de la vie quotidienne d’une copropriété (4 CE units)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-19610" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Career &amp; Professional Develop. (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">School of Continuing Studies</a>)</p>
          <p>Administered by: <a href="/study/2014-2015/node/619">Centre for Continuing Education</a></p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Business              : Ce cours permet d’acquérir les connaissances et compétences nécessaires pour la gestion d’opérations quotidiennes incluant le développement de politiques et procédures internes,  la tenue de registres, la gestion de contrats et l’organisation des réunions. L’étudiant apprendra à communiquer avec les intervenants internes et externes et à résoudre les conflits.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Summer 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Supplementary information: 30 heures en classe plus environ 10 heures de lecture supplémentaire et travaux de cours.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

